Script below is one of a simple way to checksum of a file and get the report immediately.
#!/usr/bin/bash # syntax: ./checksum.sh &lt;algorithm&gt; &lt;file&gt; &lt;cert&gt; diff &lt;(echo -n $($1 $2 | cut -d &#39; &#39; -f 1)) $3 -s Here I named the script checksum.sh but you can name it however you want.
It&rsquo;s pretty straightforward script, if you want to learn more about the command used in the script, you can copy the content and paste it in explainshell.
